.TH "vxge_hw_fifo_txdl_buffer_set" 9 "vxge_hw_fifo_txdl_buffer_set" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vxge_hw_fifo_txdl_buffer_set \- Set transmit buffer pointer in the descriptor.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" vxge_hw_fifo_txdl_buffer_set
.BI "(struct __vxge_hw_fifo *fifo "  ","
.BI "void *txdlh "  ","
.BI "u32 frag_idx "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t dma_pointer "  ","
.BI "u32 size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "fifo" 12
Handle to the fifo object used for non offload send
.IP "txdlh" 12
Descriptor handle.
.IP "frag_idx" 12
Index of the data buffer in the caller's scatter-gather list
(of buffers).
.IP "dma_pointer" 12
DMA address of the data buffer referenced by \fIfrag_idx\fP.
.IP "size" 12
Size of the data buffer (in bytes).
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This API is part of the preparation of the transmit descriptor for posting
(via \fBvxge_hw_fifo_txdl_post\fP). The related "preparation" APIs include
\fBvxge_hw_fifo_txdl_mss_set\fP and \fBvxge_hw_fifo_txdl_cksum_set_bits\fP.
All three APIs fill in the fields of the fifo descriptor,
in accordance with the Titan specification.
